entries.title: The rest of Messi's career will play out with satisfaction - however long he stays on the pitch
entries.description: When the crowning moment came, after an epic World Cup final, it was not the blue-and-white striped Argentina shirt fully visible on Lionel Messi.

entries.title: 'Immense joy': Hundred of thousands of fans fill streets of Buenos Aires to celebrate World Cup win
entries.description: Argentina's triumph in the World Cup final has sent hundreds of thousands of ecstatic fans pouring out onto the streets of Buenos Aires.

entries.title: Fairytale ending for Messi – Argentina beat France in penalty shootout to win World Cup
entries.description: Argentina have won the World Cup after a thrilling final which saw them take the lead and then lose it again twice before winning a penalty shootout.

entries.title: China 'a significant threat' to UK and dependency should be curbed, MPs warn
entries.description: China poses "a significant threat" to the UK and the government should move to curb its dependence on the superpower to enable it to respond to aggression or abuses by Beijing, MPs have said.

Pitch invader images released after Australia football violence where goalie attacked
entries.description: Australian police have released images of people they want to trace after "shocking" violence erupted at a football match.

entries.title: Teenager charged with people-smuggling offence after four died while crossing Channel
entries.description: A teenager has been charged with a people-smuggling offence after four people died while attempting to cross the Channel.

entries.title: 'A Christmas miracle': Katherine Jenkins' lost dress turns up minutes before Pope concert
entries.description: Katherine Jenkins' show for Pope Francis did go on after all yesterday evening, after lost luggage almost scuppered her appearance at the pontiff's Christmas concert.

entries.title: Ukraine picks Eurovision entry after competition in underground bunker
entries.description: Ukraine has chosen its entry for next year's Eurovision song contest after shortlisted acts performed in an underground bunker as the deadly Russian assault continued above.

entries.title: Less than 9% of voters turn out for Tunisia election
entries.description: Just 8.8% of Tunisia's voters took part in elections on Saturday amid ongoing anger at President Kais Saied.

entries.title: Israel deports Palestinian activist to France despite Paris objections
entries.description: Israel has deported a Jerusalem-born Palestinian activist to France, despite objections by Paris.

entries.title: World Cup final: Five things to know as France and Argentina prepare for title clash
entries.description: The World Cup is nearing its end, with France and Argentina to meet in the final match later today.
